          <dl>
                          <dt>Medium</dt>
              <dd>Leaded bronze</dd>
            
           
                        <dt>Technique</dt>
             <dd>Cast, lost-wax process</dd>
           
                          <dt>Dimensions</dt>
              <dd>10.7 x 6.7 x 1 cm (4 3/16 x 2 5/8 x 3/8 in.)</dd>
            
                          <dt>Technical Details</dt>
              <dd>
                                                      <p class="divider">Chemical Composition: XRF data from Tracer<br />
Alloy: Leaded Bronze<br />
Alloying Elements: copper, tin, lead<br />
Other Elements: iron, mercury<br />
K. Eremin, January 2014</p>
                                      <p class="divider">Technical Observations: The patina consists of patches of red cuprite over greenish brown, while burial dirt and bare metal are featured on the interior. Holes are present in both halves.<br />
 <br />
The two halves of the cross and the loop for hanging were cast separately and are held together by a pin with hammered ends. Rough finishing marks are evident on the inside edges of the crosses. The designs and inscriptions were engraved.<br />
 <br />
 <br />
Carol Snow  (submitted 2002)</p>
                                                </dd>
            
            
            
            
